# 8-bit ALU RTL Design, Synthesis and STA

## Objective

Design an 8-bit ALU in Verilog, synthesize it to a gate-level netlist,
perform gate-level simulation, and analyze timing using Static Timing Analysis (STA).

## Tools Used

- Verilog HDL
- Yosys
- OpenSTA
- Icarus Verilog / ModelSim
- Nangate45 Liberty Library

## Design Flow

RTL Design
    ↓
Functional Simulation
    ↓
Synthesis (Yosys)
    ↓
Gate-Level Netlist
    ↓
Gate-Level Simulation
    ↓
Static Timing Analysis (OpenSTA)

## Files

### RTL

- rtl/alu8.v

### Testbench

- tb/tb_alu8.v

### Synthesis

- synthesis/synth.ys
- synthesis/alu8_netlist.v

### Constraints

- constraints/alu8.sdc

### STA

- sta/sta.tcl
- sta/timing_report.rpt

## STA Results

| Metric | Value |
|----------|--------|
| WNS | -0.42 ns |
| TNS | -1.15 ns |
| Hold Slack | +0.15 ns |

## Timing Violation Fixes

- Pipeline insertion
- Logic optimization
- Re-synthesis with timing-driven optimization

## Conclusion

The RTL and gate-level simulations match functionally.
STA identified a setup timing violation which can be fixed through pipelining and optimization.
